HB475 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2 Relating to the Public Service Commission; to establish
3 the Power to the People Act; to amend Sections 37-1-1, 37-1-3,
4 37-1-5, and 37-1-12, Code of Alabama 1975; to revise the
5 membership and terms of the public service commissioners; to
6 establish the Secretary of Energy as a cabinet member
7 appointed by the Governor and provide for the duties of the
8 secretary; to add Sections 37-1-81.1, 37-1-81.2, and 37-1-81.3
9 to the Code of Alabama 1975, to prohibit an increase in
10 electric retail base rates for a certain period and thereafter
11 prohibit electric utilities from including certain costs in
12 the calculation or determination of rates or service
13 regulations; to require the commission to hold a public
14 meeting at least annually; to provide for rate hearings in
15 certain circumstances; to amend Sections 17-14-2, 17-14-3, and
16 36-3-1, Code of Alabama 1975, to make conforming changes; to
17 repeal Section 37-1-9, Code of Alabama 1975, relating to
18 public service commissioners; and to make nonsubstantive,
19 technical revisions to update the existing code language to
20 current style.
21 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
22 Section 1. This act shall be known and may be cited as
23 the Power to the People Act.
24 Section 2. Sections 37-1-1, 37-1-3, 37-1-5, and
25 37-1-12, Code of Alabama 1975, are amended to read as follows:
26 "§37-1-1
27 A commission to be known as the Public Service
28 Commission, consisting of a president and two associates who
