141 "§37-1-5
142 (a) No public service commissioner or clerk Public
143 service commissioners, the Secretary of Energy, the spouse and
144 children of any commissioner or the secretary, and employees
145 of the commission shall, during his continuance in office,
146 personally or through any partner or agent, may not render any
147 professional paid service for public utilities.
148 (b) A utility regulated by the Public Service
149 Commission may not make a contribution to any candidate
150 running for the office of a public service commissioner.
151 (c) The commissioners shall be subject to the ethics
152 laws under Chapter 25 of Title 36.
153 (d) No commissioner, for a fee, reward, or other
154 compensation, in addition to that received in his or her
155 official capacity, shall represent any person before the
156 Legislature or any executive department or agency."
157 "§37-1-12
158 (a)(1) Beginning January 19, 2027, the position of
159 Secretary of Energy is created as a member of the Governor's
160 cabinet. The secretary shall be appointed by and serve at the
161 pleasure of the Governor. The secretary's salary shall be
162 fixed by the Governor and shall not be subject to Section
163 36-6-6. The secretary must have experience in utility
164 regulation or energy policy or a related field.
165 (2) The Secretary of Energy shall direct the activities
166 of the commission and shall set the agendas for all meetings
167 of the commissioners, provided a meeting agenda may be amended
168 by the affirmative vote of at least five commissioners.
Page 6

by the affirmative vote of at least five commissioners.
